To assess day-to-day stability of meal timing, the Composite Phase Deviation (CPD) metric was applied to the first, midpoint, and last daily caloric event. The CPD combines two components: (i) how different meal timing is compared to that on the previous day (regularity component) and (ii) how far away it is from the daily mean (alignment component)29. CPD scores reflect the average deviation in hours from a perfectly regular pattern of meal timing (i.e., same time every day).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
